<h2>Tabs in setup page</h2>
<br>
<div class="accordion">
<h3>Slider Main Info</h3>
<div>
<p><span  style='font-weight:bold;'>Consist of main slider settings.</span> Commonly all fields are clear. In this area you can setup such fields :<br>
<ul style='list-style-type: disc;'>
<li>Full Width - show slider in full width mode.</li>
<li>Full Screen - show slider in full screen mode.</li>
<li>Slide Processing Show - show time-indicator of current main slide.</li>
<li>Project Name - name of current poject.</li>
<li>Width - width of outter box.</li>
<li>Height - height of outter box.</li>
<li>Active Area Width - width of inner box.</li>
<li>Active Area Height - height of inner box.</li>
<li>Active Area Offset Left - left property (left offset) of inner box.</li>
<li>Active Area Offset Top - top property (top offset) of inner box.</li>
<li>Vertical Align - vertical alignment of inner box.</li>
<li>Horizontal Align - horizontal alignment of inner box.</li>
<li>Effect - choose effect for main slider.</li>
<li>Duration - duration between slides of main slider.</li>
<li>Effect Duration - duration of effect which changes slides.</li>
<li>Direction - direction of slides move.</li>
<li>Apply Classes - field for CSS description.</li>
</ul>
</p>
<h4><span  style='font-weight:bold;'>Slides Backgrounds</span></h4>
<p>To insert new background click on "Upload" button and insert new image. It appear in "Background images settings" section.
<br><span  style='font-weight:bold;'>Single background consist of such fields :</span><br>
<ul style='list-style-type: disc;'>
<li>Name - name of background (use in select boxes).</li>
<li>Description - notes about current background and slide.</li>
<li>Url - url for current background.</li>
<li>Background image - image of current background.</li>
<li>Save this background - button to save current background.</li>
<li>Delete this background - button to delete current background.</li>
</ul>
</p>
</div>
<h3>Slider Containers</h3>
<div>
<p><span  style='font-weight:bold;'>Main part in slider setup, consist of such parts :</span><br>
<ul>
<li>Containers - settings for appropriate slide.</li>
</ul>
<span  style='font-weight:bold;'>Containers consist of :</span>
<ul style='list-style-type: circle;'>
<li>Slide main settings - main setting for appropriate slide.</li>
<li>Inner slider settings - setting for inner slider.</li>
<li>Single elements - manipulation with single group of elements.</li>
</ul>
Slide main settings include background select box.<br><br>
<span  style='font-weight:bold;'>Inner slider settings consist of :</span>
<ul style='list-style-type: disc;'>
<li>Inner slider main settings - main settings for inner slider.</li>
<li>Inner slides - groups of elements for inner slides.</li>
</ul>
<span  style='font-weight:bold;'>Inner slider main settings consist of :</span>
<ul style='list-style-type: square;'>
<li>Effect - inner slider effect.</li>
<li>Effect Direction - direction to move for inner slides.</li>
<li>Duration - duration between inner slides.</li>
<li>Effect's Duration - duration of effect for inner slides.</li>
<li>Left Offset - left offset for inner slides.</li>
<li>Top Offset - top offset for inner slides.</li>
</ul>
<span  style='font-weight:bold;'>Single Elements consist of :</span>
<ul style='list-style-type: disc;'>
<li>Source - group of elements which is source for current single element.</li>
<li>Start Delay - start delay for current single element.</li>
<li>Use Method of manipulation - method of changes for start manipulation.</li>
<li>Name - name of current single element.</li>
<li>Url - url of current single element.</li>
<li style='font-weight:bold;'>These elements mostly used with Method manipulation - "Use animation":</li>
<li>Start size % - size of single element in initial manipulation.</li>
<li>Start opacity in % - initial opacity of single element.</li>
<li>Start opacity out % - opacity of single element for initial manipulation.</li>
<li>Start position x in - initial position of single element by X axis.</li>
<li>Start position x out - position of single element by X axis for initial manipulation.</li>
<li>Start position y in - initial position of single element by Y axis.</li>
<li>Start position y out - position of single element by Y axis for initial manipulation.</li>
<li>Start duration - duration of initial manipulation of single element.</li>
<li>Start easing - easing for initial manipulation of single element.</li>
<li>Start Method - method for initial manipulation of single element (appearing method for single element).</li>
<li>Start rotation in - inital angle in degrees of single element.</li>
<li>Start rotation out - angle in degrees of single element for initial manipulation.</li>
<li>Start rotation origin - lets you modify the origin for transformations of an element (the centre of rotation).</li>
<li style='font-weight:bold;'>These elements mostly used with Method manipulation - "Use transition":</li>
<li>Perspective - set up perspective for current single element.</li>
<li>Start rotation 3d in - Defines inital 3D rotation. (Consist of : X, Y, Z, and angle)</li>
<li>Start rotation 3d out - Defines a 3D rotation for initial manipulation. (Consist of : X, Y, Z, and angle)</li>
<li>Start scale 3d in - Defines inital 3D scale transformation. (Consist of : sX, sY, sZ). (Default 1,1,1)</li>
<li>Start scale 3d out - Defines a 3D scale transformation for initial manipulation. (Consist of : sX, sY, sZ). (Default 1,1,1)</li>
<li>Start translate 3d in - Defines initial 3D translation. (Consist of : sX, sY, sZ). Example(100px, -100px, 40px)</li>
<li>Start translate 3d out - Defines a 3D translation for initial manipulation. (Consist of : sX, sY, sZ). Example(100px, -100px, 40px)</li>
<li>Start transform3d origin - lets you modify the origin for transformations of an element (Initial - 50% 50% 0).</li>
<li style='font-weight:bold;'>Between initaial and finish manipulations there are move and delay points</li>
<li>Delay Point - delay in single element sequence.</li>
<li>Consist of duration (delay duration) and Method (don't change).</li>
<li>Move Point - manipulation in single element sequence. Consist of :</li>
<li>Use Method of manipulation - method of changes for current point manipulation.</li>
<li style='font-weight:bold;'>These elements mostly used with Method manipulation - "Use animation":</li>
<li>Size % - point manipulation of size for single element.</li>
<li>Opacity % - point manipulation of opacity for single element.</li>
<li>Position x - initial position by X for point manipulation of single element.</li>
<li>Position y - initial position by Y for point manipulation of single element.</li>
<li>Position x out - finish position by X for point manipulation of single element.</li>
<li>Position y out - finish position by Y for point manipulation of single element.</li>
<li>Duration - duration of manipulation for single element.</li>
<li>Easing - easing of manipulation for single element.</li>
<li>Method (don't change).</li>
<li>Rotation - rotation angle in degrees for point manipulation of single element.</li>
<li>Rotation origin - lets you modify the origin for transformations of an element (the centre of rotation).</li>
<li style='font-weight:bold;'>These elements mostly used with Method manipulation - "Use transition":</li>
<li>Rotation 3d - Defines point's 3D rotation. (Consist of : X, Y, Z, and angle)</li>
<li>Scale 3d - Defines point's 3D scale transformation. (Consist of : sX, sY, sZ). (Default 1,1,1)</li>
<li>Translate 3d - Defines point's 3D translation. (Consist of : sX, sY, sZ). Example(100px, -100px, 40px)</li>
<li>Transform3d origin - lets you modify the origin for transformations of an element (Initial - 50% 50% 0).</li>

<li style='font-weight:bold;'>These elements mostly used with Method manipulation - "Use animation":</li>
<li>Finish size % - finish size of single element.</li>
<li>Finish opacity % - finish opacity of single element.</li>
<li>Finish position x in - initial position of single element by X axis for finish manipulation.</li>
<li>Finish position x out - finish position of single element by X axis.</li>
<li>Finish position y in - initial position of single element by Y axis for finish manipulation.</li>
<li>Finish position y out - finish position of single element by Y axis.</li>
<li>Finish duration - duration of finish manipulation of single element.</li>
<li>Finish easing - easing for finish manipulation of single element.</li>
<li>Finish Method - method for finish manipulation of single element (finish method for single element).</li>
<li>Finish rotation - finish angle in degrees of single element.</li>
<li>Finish rotation origin - lets you modify the origin for transformations of an element (the centre of rotation).</li>
<li style='font-weight:bold;'>These elements mostly used with Method manipulation - "Use transition":</li>
<li>Finish rotation 3d - Defines finish 3D rotation. (Consist of : X, Y, Z, and angle)</li>
<li>Finish scale 3d - Defines finish 3D scale transformation. (Consist of : sX, sY, sZ). (Default 1,1,1)</li>
<li>Finish translate 3d - Defines finish 3D translation. (Consist of : sX, sY, sZ). Example(100px, -100px, 40px)</li>
<li>Finish transform 3d origin - lets you modify the origin for transformations of an element (Example - 50% 50% 0).</li>

<li>Width - width of single element's container.</li>
<li>Height - height of single element's container. (Example: Height uses in case of initialization element position to hide it in start delay)</li>
<li>Font size - font size of single element's container.</li>
</ul>
In Single elements use sequence of manipulation. Manipulation with single element occur from last state of the element.
3D transition not supported in Opera Mini, IE8 and IE9. It has partial support in IE10 and IE11.
When you finish to change positions of containers by right arrows you need to save it by button "Save Containers Positions".
Link "Slide results" show you current slide.
</div>
<h3>Slider Items</h3>
<div>
<p>Slider Items it's source of images and texts for groups filling.<br>
<span  style='font-weight:bold;'>Consist of : "Image Items" and "Text Items".</span><br>
Image Items consist of :
<ul style='list-style-type: circle;'>
<li>Name - name of item.</li>
<li>Url - url of item.</li>
<li>Image - url to image file (for example on your server).</li>
<li>Width - width of image item (Example: width of picture to show).</li>
<li>Height - height of image item (Example: height of picture to show).</li>
<li>Offset Left - left offset of image item.</li>
<li>Offset Top - top offset of image item.</li>
<li>Group - group which this item applied to.</li>
<li>Group position - position in group (Example: Need to show correctly items in group).</li>
<li>Classes list - list of classes for current item (separated by space).</li>
</ul>
Text Items consist of :
<ul style='list-style-type: circle;'>
<li>Name - name of item.</li>
<li>Url - url of item.</li>
<li>Text - text for current item.</li>
<li>Width - width of image item (Example: width of picture to show).</li>
<li>Height - height of image item (Example: height of picture to show).</li>
<li>Offset Left - left offset of image item.</li>
<li>Offset Top - top offset of image item.</li>
<li>Group - group which this item applied to.</li>
<li>Group position - position in group (Example: Need to show correctly items in group).</li>
<li>Font size - font size for current text item.</li>
<li>Font color - font color for current text item.</li>
<li>Background color - background color for current text item.</li>
<li>Style - css for current item.</li>
<li>Classes list - list of classes for current item (separated by space).</li>
</ul>
After each item block text or image there are bulk delete block. Its work with checkboxes in the left side of each item.
</p>
</div>
<h3>Import/Export</h3>
<div>
<p>
<span  style='font-weight:bold;'>Usefull Info</span>
<br>
Before use import/export features check folder export in plugin directory for write permissions for the script. Set phar.readonly = 0 in php.ini file if absent.
<br>
<span  style='font-weight:bold;'>To Import :</span>
<br>
If you can set up in php.ini upload_max_filesize, post_max_size and max_input_time you can upload exported earlier file and execute using button upload. If you haven't access to php.ini you can upload exported earlier file into export placed in plugin directory, and choose file in the list.
<br>
<span  style='font-weight:bold;'>To Export :</span>
<br>
Just click on export button and get file in export directory.
<br>
Advice : Execute import only once when you install plugin.
</p>
</div>
